## Step 5: Verify Scaled Images & Label Alignment

```python
from PIL import Image
import glob, os

print("=== Scaled Image Sizes ===")
for path in sorted(glob.glob("dataset_scaled/train/images/*.png"))[:5]:
    img = Image.open(path)
    print(f"  {os.path.basename(path)}: {img.size}")

print("\n=== Label–Image Pairing ===")
imgs = set(os.path.splitext(f)[0]
           for f in os.listdir("dataset_scaled/train/images"))
lbls = set(os.path.splitext(f)[0]
           for f in os.listdir("dataset_scaled/train/labels"))
print(f"  Images: {len(imgs)} | Labels: {len(lbls)}")
print(f"  Images without labels: {imgs - lbls}")
print(f"  Labels without images: {lbls - imgs}")
```

